        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>synthetic inorganic red pigment [300013623], red pigment [300013533], pigment by color [300013134], pigments [300013109], colorant (material) [300013026], materials by function [300014692], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Permanent pigment  that, depending on conditions, can range in hue from orange to deep red. It is an unstable crystalline form and turns black when mixed with lead pigments. It is used in paint and to color ruby glass. It was invented and patented by Murdock in Scotland in 1847, it was replaced by cadmium red in the 1920s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047814/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種持久性強的顏料，依據情況不同，呈現的色澤範圍由橙色至深紅。為不穩定之晶體型態，與含鉛顏料混合時會變黑色。可當作繪畫顏料，也可用來替寶石紅玻璃著色。西元1847年由蘇格蘭的莫多克（Murdock）發明並申請專利，1920年代被鎘紅取代。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Permanent pigment dat afhankelijk van de omstandigheden in kleurschakering kan variëren van oranje tot dieprood. Het is een onstabiele kristallijne vorm, die zwart wordt als het pigment wordt gemengd met loodpigmenten. Het wordt gebruikt in verf en voor het kleuren van robijnglas. Het is in 1847 in Schotland uitgevonden en gepatenteerd door Murdock en werd in de jaren twintig van de 20ste eeuw vervangen door cadmiumrood.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
